<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1167,2034]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,270,1367,1393]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Adult</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[287,361,1368,1394]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="4.[154,272,1665,1689]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,269,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[188,1398,269,1636]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Adults of Ephysteris spp. 1, E. promptella (Staudinger); 2, E. subovata (Povolný); 3, E. montana sp. nov. (paratype, male); 4, E. flavida Povolný; 5, E. wenquana sp. nov. (holotype, male); 6, E. insulella (Heinemann)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181378/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number box="[343,361,1368,1394]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Length of forewing 3.9–5.0 mm. Head, thorax and tegula yellowish-white. Labial palpus strongly upcurved, second segment about 1.5 times length of third segment, covered with long grey, browntipped scales, inner surface yellowish-white; third segment light-grey, with broad brown basal and subapical rings. Antenna dark-brown on scape, other antennal articles dark-grey ringed with white basally. Forewing covered with cream, yellow-tipped scales and mottled by dark-grey scales along costal margin and termen; cilia creamy, brown-tipped. Hindwing pale-grey.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1167,2034]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,376,1607,1633]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[393,492,1608,1634]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 12" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1473,1497]" captionTargetBox="[259,1338,159,1453]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[242,1354,149,1467]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 12. Male genitalia of Ephysteris spp. 7, E. promptella (Staudinger) (slide no. L 05198); 8, E. subovata (Povolný) (slide no. L 06032); 9, E. montana sp. nov. (holotype, slide no. L 05196); 10, E. flavida Povolný (slide no. L 05190); 11, E. wenquana sp. nov. (Paratype, slide no. L 06064); 12, E. insulella (Heinemann) (slide no. L 06128)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181379/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Figs. 
<number box="[460,492,1608,1634]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="10.16">10</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[505,538,1608,1634]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="7.[151,269,810,834]" captionTargetBox="[277,1312,195,787]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[265,1322,173,800]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Male segment VIII of Ephysteris spp. 13, E. promptella (Staudinger); 14, E. subovata (Povolný); 15, E. montana sp. n.; 16, E. flavida Povolný; 17, E. wenquana sp. n.; 18, E. insulella (Heinemann)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181380/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">16</figureCitation>
). Posterior margin of sternite VIII with deep triangular incision. Uncus subtriangular, evenly narrowed apically, apex rounded. Gnathos relatively broad, sickle-shaped, with broadened apex. Tegumen narrow. Valva at most level with base of gnathos, evenly curved inwards, slender, of equal width, apex distinctly pointed; sacculus narrow, slightly exceeding half length of valva; paired process on posterior margin of vinculum short, subtriangular, rounded apically, medial incision deep, triangular. Saccus basally broad, triangular, distal portion very slender. Phallus about as long as tegumen, basal quarter rounded, slightly inflated, distal portion relatively slender, straight, evenly tapered with small subapical teeth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1167,2034]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,152,778]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,404,1887,1913]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[420,509,1888,1914]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 24" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1932,1956]" captionTargetBox="[293,1333,212,1862]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[224,1358,194,1895]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 24. Female genitalia of Ephysteris spp. 19, E. promptella (Staudinger) (slide no. L 06106); 20, E. subovata (Povolný) (slide no. L 06033); 21, E. montana sp. nov. (holotype, slide no. L 05197); 22, E. flavida Povolný (slide no. L 05184); 23, E. wenquana sp. nov. (paratype, slide no. L 06086); 24, E. insulella (Heinemann) (slide no. L 05194)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/181381/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="52">
Fig. 
<number box="[476,509,1888,1914]" pageId="7" pageNumber="52" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
). Apophyses anteriores straight, short. Segment VIII trapezoid, twice length of apophyses anteriores, posterior margin weakly curved anteriorly, with moderately broad suboval membranous zone between subgenital plates, which distinctly narrowed and prolonged anteromedially around ostium bursae, ostial zone covered with minute spines. Ductus bursae slender, evenly broadened near corpus bursae; antrum slightly longer than apophyses anteriores. Corpus bursae large, broadened proximally; signum a subtriangular plate, about as long as broad, with distinctly prolonged, narrow and pointed basal corners, medial process narrow, its proximal part shorter than basal corners of signum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,152,778]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,271,297]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Variation.</emphasis>
All examined specimens show slight variation in the extent of yellowish patches on forewing; the sacculus varies slightly in width; the vinculum lobes may be triangular, pointed apically, or rounded; the length of apophyses anteriores varies from half to two-thirds the length of segment VIII.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,1383,391,418]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,152,778]" box="[197,1383,391,418]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,298,391,417]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Biology.</emphasis>
