<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,152,778]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,511,537]" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[327,759,512,537]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ephysteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavida" subGenus="Microcraspedus">
<emphasis box="[327,759,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">Ephysteris (Microcraspedus) flavida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognizable externally by the yellowish-white forewing with dark costal margin, but may occasionally be confused with yellowish-coloured 
<taxonomicName authority="Povolny" authorityName="Povolny" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ephysteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosa" subGenus="Microcraspedus">
<emphasis box="[1182,1374,552,577]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">E. (M.) speciosa</emphasis>
Povolný
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Povolny. The" authorityName="Povolny. The" box="[262,626,592,618]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ephysteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chretieni" subGenus="Microcraspedus">
<emphasis box="[262,458,592,617]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">E. (M.) chretieni</emphasis>
Povolný. The
</taxonomicName>
male genitalia are characterized by the slender, evenly curved valva not expanded apically, the short, paired process on the posterior margin of the vinculum, and the slender distal portion of the phallus. The female genitalia resemble particularly those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1032,1239,672,697]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ephysteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="treskensis" subGenus="Microcraspedus">
<emphasis box="[1032,1239,672,697]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">E. (M.) treskensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ephysteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispanica" subGenus="Microcraspedus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">E. (M.) hispanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[254,482,712,737]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Ephysteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diminutella" subGenus="Microcraspedus">
<emphasis box="[254,482,712,737]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="53">E. (M.) diminutella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differ in the broader, subtriangular signum and the ostial zone with minute spines.
</paragraph>
